Darius Gill
National Practice Director

 

Darius is the National Practice Leader for our Foundation and Institutional Advisory Services (FIA) segment.  FIA provides Outsourced Chief Investment Officer (OCIO) services to non profits across the country.  Functionally, Darius leads a team of investment professionals and asset servicing experts who specialize in helping institutional clients design, build and implement investment strategies consistent with the goals of their organization.  Prior to joining Northern Trust, Darius was a Chief Investment Officer with another financial organization.  Darius has over  25 years experience in the investment industry in both the institutional and high-net worth sides of the business. Academically, Darius earned a Bachelor of Science degree from the University Of Wisconsin at Madison, and subsequently was awarded an M.B.A. from the Kellstadt Graduate School of Business at DePaul University.  In his professional affiliation, Darius is a member of the Investment Analysts Society of Chicago and has been awarded the C.F.A. (Chartered Financial Analyst) designation.Darius and his wife Elizabeth live in Clarendon Hills.  Both Darius and Elizabeth are active in charitable and civic activities.











